        "title": "Compare two dates in Java, without compareTo",
        "body": "<p>I'm writing my own <code>compareTo<\/code> method to compare two dates. How would I go about doing this?<\/p>\n\n<p>I've thought about this question before, using tons of if statements, but there has to be a better way.<\/p>\n\n<p>Any ideas?<\/p>\n",
