    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/jXcg4.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 1263831,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1221571,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1221571/eran",
                "reputation": 395099,
                "display_name": "Eran",
                "accept_rate": 67
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1415031796,
            "creation_date": 1415031796,
            "body": "<p>If you are referring to java.util.Date, just do <code>date1.getTime() &lt; date2.getTime()<\/code>. A simple comparison of long values.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 26718447,
            "question_id": 26718422
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/HLTev.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 3557625,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2970947,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2970947/elliott-frisch",
                "reputation": 201916,
                "display_name": "Elliott Frisch"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1415032060,
            "creation_date": 1415032060,
            "body": "<p>There are three methods that might help <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Date.html#before(java.util.Date)\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>Date.before(Date)<\/code><\/a>, <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Date.html#after(java.util.Date)\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>Date.after(Date)<\/code><\/a> and <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Date.html#equals(java.lang.Object)\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>Date.equals(Date)<\/code><\/a> you could do something like<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static int compareTo(Date a, Date b) {\n  if (a.equals(b)) return 0;\n  return (a.before(b) ? -1 : 1);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 26718527,
            "question_id": 26718422
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/1V5SP.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 449256,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 843943,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/843943/grim",
                "reputation": 2163,
                "display_name": "Grim",
                "accept_rate": 75
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1415031980,
            "creation_date": 1415031980,
            "body": "<p>This is a good start:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class MyComparator extends Comparator&lt;Date&gt; {\n    public int compare(Date o1, Date o2){\n        return o1.getTime() - o2.getTime();\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>For example:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>TreeSet&lt;Date&gt; ts = new TreeSet&lt;Date&gt;(new MyComparator());\nts.add(new Date(98796541));\nts.add(new Date(59586541));\nSystem.out.println(\"Earlier is \" + ts.first());\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
